76561198131559915,Recommended,271760,20100719,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,aringt,"I need to update this review. I had been messing around with the windows Icons for a while. Some games have problems with Win 7 and Win 10 due to the fact that the Operating Systems has changed the way the Mouse Device Context works and sometimes you have to reduce the game into windows mode to get the mouse cursor to work with the mouse. That happened with the game ""Titan Quest."" But, I could not find such feature on the Dungeon Lords icon on the startup bar. So I went directly to the DL Steam Edition application exe. file and right clicked and brought up the properties panel. Went to the Compatability tab and changed the compatability mode for Win XP Service Pack 3 and checked the boxes for Disable display scaling on high DPI settings and Run as Administrator. That fixed the problems. So far, the start of the game came out without a hitch.I actually like how the options and charater creation had been rearanged and looks alot better than the original set up UI. Now, hope the game plays as well, or even better, than the Collectors Edition was. Really loved playing this game.BTW, when you start with the messenger, before you move anywheres, save the game. Then go to the chest that is behind the ruins wall and open it. If you do not get the bow, keep reloading and going to the chest untill you finally recieved the bow. After that, get on the rock that is west of your area and get on it. Keep on shooting the enemies and building up your acrobatics as well as some other needed skills ... acrobatics, on the 4th level will let your character make a jump backwardsflip so he can get on the rock much quicker before more enemies come. This can build your skills up as well as collect money and other items that will help you in your quest. Yea, it will take some time to get all that up to snuff, but it's worth it."
