,Recommended,271760,24455257,"Posted: 22 July, 2016",all,Andarius,"I've played this game before, back when it first came out. I've had a similar experience now as I did then, pleasant. It's a nice mix of Third Person and Adventure-Dungeon crawl RPG. Level design is good, the controls are responsive, combat is somewhat fast paced but it has a good system with the possibility to either block attacks or attack, depending on your click, similar to Gothic. The difficulty is hard enough not to get booring and you can even adjust the frequency of random encounters of mobs. Works well on 1920x1080 resolution, not to mention it makes the game look a lot more visually appealing. Another interesting thing about it is that you can revive after you die and you lose a a random stat by doing so.Now I haven't played this game too much so I can't really think of any CONS right now other than not having a way to escape persuing mobs that are faster or just as fast as you without running outside that area."
76561198038436383,Recommended,271760,27053198,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,knollie,"You really need to give this game a try. If you like jumping or logic (straight forward ones) puzzles, chests that take skill to pick, loot and the option to team up with friends, this game is for you.Multiplayer is a little glitchy. For the thieve's quest, ensure you head to Cutard Manner before you do anything else and complete it before you quite for the day. Generally, all quest related items, by default, end up in the host's inventory (on LAN, not sure about online). Let the host grab all the quest related things, sometimes he is the only one that will be able to activate certain things. If you begin an area, like Skulldoon, try to finish it in a single play, doing so will avoid conflicts or glitches with the quest item issue. If you follow this rule, then anyone in the party will be able to use quest items.May seem a little quirky, but the game is fun with friends and has an interesting skill / magic system.One last thing, if a quest does not seem to be working, have everyone in the group speak to the quest giver, even if it is not your quest, this seems to allow at least one perosn in the party to complete the quest, if something goes wrong."
